Integral Cryptanalysis

Square Attack - Integral Cryptanalysis

  • It is a Chosen Plaintext Attack proposed on SQUARE Block Cipher by Daemen.
  • Similar to Differential but here we use a Set of Plaintexts known as Delta Set Δ\DeltaΔ﻿ instead of just two.

All Property (A)(\mathcal{A})(A)﻿

  • The Byte Cell of the State Matrix of all the Plaintexts in the Plaintext Set Δ\DeltaΔ﻿ that exhausts all the possible values from {0,1}8\{0,1\}^8{0,1}8﻿ which appear exactly once is said to have All Property
  • Basically that Byte Cell in the Initial Delta Set that we chose to take all the values from {0,1}8\{0,1\}^8{0,1}8﻿ has All Property

Constant Property (C)(\mathcal{C})(C)﻿

  • The Byte Cell of the State Matrix of all the Plaintexts in the Plaintext Set Δ\DeltaΔ﻿ that has the same value across the Set is said to have Constant Property
  • Basically all the remaining Byte Cells in the Initial Delta Set Δ\DeltaΔ﻿ have the Constant Property

Balanced Property (B)(\mathcal{B})(B)﻿

  • The Byte Cell of the State Matrix of all the Plaintexts in the Plaintext Set Δ\DeltaΔ﻿ that leads to 000﻿ when an XOR\text{XOR}XOR﻿ sum is done across the Set is said to have Balance Property
  • All the All property cells (A)(\mathcal{A})(A)﻿ also have Balance Property.
    • This is because while summing from LSB\text{LSB}LSB﻿ to MSB\text{MSB}MSB﻿ every Bit across the whole 256256 256﻿ Plaintexts will be divided into 128128128﻿ 000﻿ bits, and 128128 128﻿ 11 1﻿ Bits, so they have even parity.
    • XOR\text{XOR}XOR﻿ of 128128 128﻿ 000﻿'s will lead to 000﻿ and XOR\text{XOR}XOR﻿ of 128128128﻿ 111﻿'s leads to 000﻿ so in total 000﻿
  • All the Constant Property Cells (C)(\mathcal{C})(C)﻿ also have Balance Property.
    • This is because XOR\text{XOR}XOR﻿ operation over the a constant ccc﻿ even number of times (256)(256)(256)﻿ will lead to 000﻿

Delta Set (Δ)(\Delta)(Δ)﻿

  • We will be taking a Set of 256 Plaintexts called Delta Set (Δ)(\Delta)(Δ)﻿ where one byte of each plaintext takes all values from {0,1}8\{0,1\}^8{0,1}8﻿ and the rest of the bytes have constant values.
    • In case of Kalyna 128128128﻿ Bit Block we get the following
  • The Initial Plaintext Set Δ\DeltaΔ﻿ in terms of A\mathcal{A}A﻿, C\mathcal{C}C﻿ and B\mathcal{B}B﻿
  • The Basic Intuition of Integral Cryptanalysis involves studying the Properties of Δ\DeltaΔ﻿ through Kalyna using this All, Constant and Balance Property

Integral Property in Kalyna

Kalyna 128128128﻿ Block Size

  • We get the Balance Property in the 2nd2^{nd}2nd﻿ round itself unlike in AES\text{AES}AES﻿ where we get the Balance property in the 3rd3^{rd}3rd﻿ round after the Mix Columns

Mix Column - Balance Property (B)(\mathcal{B})(B)﻿ Relation

  • This is because, whenever we get more than one All Property (A)(\mathcal{A})(A)﻿ cell in a column, the Mix Column of the Resultant Column would lead to Balance Property (B)(\mathcal{B})(B)﻿ in every cell in the column.
  • In the above case after 2nd2^{nd}2nd﻿ round Shift Rows SR2\text{SR}_2SR2​﻿, we have 444﻿ All Property (A)(\mathcal{A})(A)﻿ cells per column. Hence the next operation Mix Column leads to Balance Property (B)(\mathcal{B})(B)﻿ in every cell in all the columns of the State Matrix.

Proof

  • Without Loss of Generality Let's calculate the Mix Columns for the First Column
  • After 2nd2^{nd}2nd﻿ round Shift Rows SR2\text{SR}_2SR2​﻿ let the below Column be the First Column of the ithi^{th}ith﻿ Plaintext in the Delta Set Δ\DeltaΔ﻿
  • Now applying the Mix Column over this output we get
  • Without Loss of generality lets take the First Cell b0\mathtt{b_0}b0​﻿ after Mix Columns for the ithi^{th}ith﻿, we get
  • Doing the XOR\text{XOR}XOR﻿ sum for all the Plaintexts in the delta set Δ\DeltaΔ﻿ for the first cell b0\mathtt{b_0}b0​﻿ we get
  • Hence for the First Cell b0\mathtt{b_0}b0​﻿ we get the Balance Property and similarly for other cells in the Column
  • Now we need more than one All property cell (A)(\mathcal{A})(A)﻿ in a column because if there is only one the Mix Columns would diffuse the All property to other cells in the column - making it a All property Column not a Balance Property Column.
    • If there are more than one, the combination of these All property cells will not necessarily diffuse to a All Property Cell, but the Balance Property will be retained, hence leading to the diffusion of Balance Property in the entire column.

Kalyna 256256256﻿ Block Size

  • Similar to 128128128﻿ Kalyna Block, we get the Balance Property in 2nd2^{nd}2nd﻿ round

Kalyna 512512512﻿ Block Size

  • However in case of 512512512﻿ Kalyna Block Size - we get the Balance Property in 3rd3^{rd}3rd﻿ Round instead of 2nd2^{nd}2nd﻿ round like in previous cases, this can be explained from the above Mix Column - Balance Property proof.
  • This is because after 2nd2^{nd}2nd﻿ round Shift Rows SR2\text{SR}_2SR2​﻿ we get only one All property cell (A)(\mathcal{A})(A)﻿ per column hence the Mix Column only diffuses the All property to the whole column, not the Balance Property as explained in the proof.
  • After the 3rd3^{rd}3rd﻿ round Shift Rows SR3\text{SR}_3SR3​﻿ however we have more than one All property cell (A)(\mathcal{A})(A)﻿ per column hence Mix Column Diffuses the Balance Property to the whole column.
